# Environment Variables

- Configuration files must use environment variables
- Never commit sensitive environment variables to source control.
- Use a `.env` file for local development.
- Document all required environment variable in the README.md file.

# Security

- Production API URLS must not be committed to source code.
- Use the environment variable for all sensitive configuration.
- Keep credentials and API keys secure and never expose them in client-side code.